This directory contains Android resource files used by the Regalia app.

NOTE on README.license placement:
  Android's AAPT2 resource merger strictly requires every file directly
  inside res/ subfolders to end in .xml, .png, .webp, or .9.png. Plain-text
  files like README.license fail this validation, so per-subfolder
  README.license files cannot live inside res/values/, res/xml/, or
  res/mipmap-*/. Instead, this single README.license at the res/ root
  documents the license for ALL res/ subfolders. The same license
  information is also mirrored in src/main/README.license.

Subdirectory license summary:
  - values/: AGPL v3 (original)
      strings.xml — application name ("Regalia v1.1.0") and string
      resources. Contains app_name, dialog titles, button labels,
      toast messages, ECO family names, and all user-facing strings
      in both Chinese and English (selected at runtime via _lang).
      (v1.0.8 PHASE 30: updated from stale "Regalia v1.0.3" reference.)
  - xml/: AGPL v3 (original)
      network_security_config.xml — TLS 1.2+ enforcement + cleartext
      block for HTTPS connections to the Lichess Tablebase API.
      The config disables cleartext traffic entirely and trusts the
      system CA store; TlsSecurityHelper.java additionally enforces
      TLS 1.2+ via SSLSocketFactory on API 21-27 where the system
      default might negotiate TLS 1.0/1.1.
      v1.0.3: no changes.
      v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev17: backup_rules.xml and data_extraction_rules.xml
      added. backup_rules.xml (<full-backup-content>) declares the
      sharedpref domain and app_webview/Local Storage/ directory as
      user data to be preserved during cloud backup.
      data_extraction_rules.xml (<data-extraction-rules>, Android 12+)
      mirrors this for cloud-backup and device-transfer scenarios.
      Referenced by AndroidManifest.xml's android:fullBackupContent and
      android:dataExtractionRules attributes.
  - mipmap-hdpi/ ... mipmap-xxxhdpi/: AGPL v3 (AI-generated assets)
      App launcher icons (ic_launcher, ic_launcher_round,
      ic_launcher_foreground) in 5 density buckets (hdpi, mdpi, xhdpi,
      xxhdpi, xxxhdpi). All icons are AI-generated and licensed under
      AGPL v3 — NOT derived from DroidFish or Stockfish. The ic_launcher
      foreground depicts a gold crown on a dark rounded-square
      background, matching the in-app ♔ header logo.
      v1.0.3: no changes.

Overall, all resources in this directory tree are original works licensed
under AGPL v3. No DroidFish-derived or Stockfish-derived resources are
present here.

See the root-level LICENSE-AGPL v3, LICENSE-GPL v3, and NOTICE files
for full license texts and attribution details.

